---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Installation">
  <h1>Installation</h1>

  <h2>Python SDK</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>pip install entdb-sdk</code></pre>
  <p>Or with <code>uv</code>:</p>
  <pre is:raw><code>uv add entdb-sdk</code></pre>

  <h2>Go SDK</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>go get github.com/elloloop/tenant-shard-db/sdk/go/entdb@latest</code></pre>

  <h2>Server (Docker)</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code># Pull the latest image
docker pull ghcr.io/elloloop/entdb:latest

# Run with default settings (in-memory WAL, local storage)
docker run -p 50051:50051 ghcr.io/elloloop/entdb:latest</code></pre>

  <h2>Server (Docker Compose)</h2>
  <p>For production with Kafka WAL and S3 storage:</p>
  <pre is:raw><code>git clone https://github.com/elloloop/tenant-shard-db.git
cd tenant-shard-db
docker compose up -d</code></pre>
  <p>This starts EntDB + Redpanda (Kafka) + MinIO (S3) + Redpanda Console.</p>

  <h2>From Source</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>git clone https://github.com/elloloop/tenant-shard-db.git
cd tenant-shard-db

# Install server
pip install -e .

# Install SDK
pip install -e ./sdk

# Run server
entdb</code></pre>

  <h2>Verify Installation</h2>
  <pre is:raw><code>python -c "
import asyncio
from entdb_sdk import DbClient

async def check():
    async with DbClient('localhost:50051') as db:
        health = await db.health()
        print(health)

asyncio.run(check())
"</code></pre>

  <h2>Requirements</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Component</th><th>Requirement</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Python</td><td>&ge; 3.10</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Go</td><td>&ge; 1.21</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Docker</td><td>&ge; 20.10</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Server RAM</td><td>&ge; 256 MB (0.25 vCPU works)</td></tr>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
